stylometry: The concept of safety stock is so that you can always meet demand incase of a sudden increase or rush of orders for a product. Saftey stock is the inventory that you have on-hand that exceeds your expected rate of demand as a buffer (saftey net) so that if demand spikes you can still fill all the requests for product and make sales. It is important because if you do not have any and you do get a spike in demand but cannot meet those orders; you lose sales, which means you lose money, you piss off customers who can't get what they want, and that in-turn loses you more future sales when they don't return because you made them mad. It is always better to be prepared for an increase in demand then to run out of things to sell to willingly paying customers.
